Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Submit Claim, Validate Claim Documents
   Explanation: The use case "Validate Claim Documents" is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Submit Claim"). It is not associated with any actor directly — no actor interacts with it. It does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and is neither a generalization nor a specialization. "Validate Claim Documents" does not represent a complete, independently meaningful service to any actor; it is merely a decomposed sub-step of the "Submit Claim" process. This is a classic instance of Functional Decomposition via the include relationship, where a use case's internal behavior has been improperly extracted into a separate inclusion use case that serves no standalone purpose.
